specs/yoga/quota-system.rst.message:
Yes, but suppress is meant to suppress exceptions, though it behaves as a null context if no exception is provided. To make the distinction clear Python added the nullcontext on Python 3.7 [1], so we use our custom nullcontext until we only support Python >= 3.7 in Cinder and then change it to the contextlib.nullcontext, which is a clearer change in the code self.nullcontext => contextlib.nullcontext. The current silly nullcontext implementation:

    @contextlib.contextmanager
    def nullcontext(*args, **kwargs):
        yield None

[1]: https://docs.python.org/3/library/contextlib.html#contextlib.nullcontext
